### Description

Using `transformedValue` from @angular/forms/signals in a component that also provides `NG_VALUE_ACCESSOR` (to support legacy reactive forms / ngModel) causes a circular dependency error (NG0200) at runtime when the component is used with the [formField] directive.

**Steps to Reproduce**
1. Create a component that implements both ControlValueAccessor and FormValueControl<T>
2. Provide NG_VALUE_ACCESSOR in the component's providers array (needed to support ngModel / formControl usage)
3. Use transformedValue as a class field to manage display-vs-model value transformation
4. Use the component in a template with [formField] binding

```
@Component({
  selector: 'my-input',
  providers: [
    {
      provide: NG_VALUE_ACCESSOR,
      useExisting: forwardRef(() => MyInputComponent),
      multi: true,
    },
  ],
})
export class MyInputComponent
  implements ControlValueAccessor, FormValueControl<number | null>
{
  public value = model<number | null>(null);

  // This line causes NG0200 when [formField] is used on this component
  public raw = transformedValue(this.value, {
    format: (v) => v?.toString() ?? null,
    parse: (v) => ({ value: v ? parseFloat(v) : null }),
  });

  // ControlValueAccessor methods...
  writeValue(value: number | null) { ... }
  registerOnChange(fn: any) { ... }
  registerOnTouched(fn: any) { ... }
}
```

